# Day 31 – AI Supply Chain Control Tower using Claude AI

## Objective

The objective of this task was to build an interactive AI Supply Chain Control Tower that simulates real-world supply chain operations. The application helps users make operational decisions by managing alerts, monitoring business KPIs, and optimizing overall supply chain performance.

## Project Summary

* Application: AI Supply Chain Control Tower
* Technology: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
* Type: Interactive Operations Management Simulator
* Goal: Improve operational performance by making strategic supply chain decisions.

## Features Implemented

* Interactive operations dashboard
* Live KPI monitoring
* Random operational alerts
* Priority-based incident management
* Multiple corrective action options
* Dynamic KPI updates
* Live event log
* Countdown timer
* Performance score tracking
* Final operational dashboard
* Pause and Help functionality
* Responsive user interface
* Replay simulation

## Operational Alerts

The simulator generates various supply chain incidents including:

* Port Congestion
* Supplier Delay
* Truck Breakdown
* Warehouse Stock Shortage
* Customs Inspection
* Demand Spike
* Factory Machine Failure
* Weather Disruption
* Inventory Mismatch
* Damaged Shipment

## Key Performance Indicators

The dashboard continuously tracks:

* Service Level
* Customer Satisfaction
* Inventory Health
* Transportation Efficiency
* Operating Cost
* Revenue Protected
* Overall Score

## Key Learnings

* Supply chain management requires balancing multiple priorities simultaneously.
* Every operational decision directly impacts business performance.
* Data-driven decision-making improves efficiency and customer satisfaction.
* AI can simplify complex operations through interactive simulations and dashboards.

## Conclusion

This project provided practical experience in supply chain operations by simulating real-time business challenges. Claude AI helped transform operational concepts into an engaging, interactive learning experience while strengthening my front-end development and problem-solving skills.
